    Example of a Longitudinal Biomarker Study

    longitudinal_biomarker_study.Rd

    Targeted selected reaction monitoring analysis. Time points A, B, C, and D increase in the corresponding order. A & B are prior to the disease diagnosis for the cases. C & D are correspondingly after the diagnosis. Time point D is after the treatment.

    data("longitudinal_biomarker_study")

    Format

    An MSnSet with 300 features and 236 samples.

    Source

    xxx study

    pData

    A data frame consisting of 236 rows (samples) and 12 columns:

    Sample

    The sample identifier. This is the SubjID and TimePoint concatenated with an underscore.

    isQC

    TRUE if the sample is a quality control sample.

    MatchID

    The unique subject identifier.

    Type

    "Control" or "Case".

    Plate

    The microplate identifier. Either "01", "02", "03", or "04".

    Well

    The microplate well location. PlateRow concatenated with PlateCol.

    PlateRow

    The row of the microplate where the sample is located. Letters A-H.

    PlateCol

    The column of the microplate where the sample is located. Strings "02" to "12".

    TimePoint

    Time point: A, B, C, or D.

    Days

    Number of days since disease diagnosis.

    SubjID

    Subject ID. This is the MatchID and a letter representing the Type ("C" for Control and "D" for Case) concatenated with an underscore.

    Age

    Subject age in years.

    fData

    A data frame consisting of 300 rows (features) and 4 columns:

    Organism

    The organism name: "YEAST", "BOVIN", or "HUMAN".

    Protein

    The gene symbol and organism name concatenated with an underscore.

    Peptide

    The peptide sequence.

    isSpike

    TRUE if Organism is "YEAST" or "BOVIN".
